<p>Centrist senator Rodrigo Paz won Bolivia’s presidential runoff on Sunday, securing about 54.6% of the vote against former interim president Jorge “Tuto” Quiroga’s 45.4%, according to the Supreme Electoral Tribunal’s preliminary count [france24.com#2][mercopress.com#1][scmp.com#1][theguardian.com#1]. The result ends nearly two decades of rule by the left-wing Movement Toward Socialism as voters, hit by fuel shortages and high inflation, opted for change amid a deep economic slump [france24.com#3][bbc.com#1]. Paz campaigned on fiscal discipline—including trimming fuel subsidies—and a “capitalism for all” approach aimed at reviving growth [france24.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]. He is set to take office on November 8 and has pledged to build consensus to govern a polarized country [reuters.com#1][france24.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/meoSGYquliK3j5akX5p3oNgwZHo6F2dSIHdrkJXIH7vNBqIgP553GBfKp34Cz7QCI8XSwhfdCLSFCMiHudQ3barazYJJZXeGR4nxro2I7nfVGoSpYiRZL71iEAceVwxT0unLp5IzG2bWfArXZbWpHScDawl-_6sfvH7cO-UtbksQi2Qc36xl60Gaw9LIwxZ0espc7rlL-KgTNITH7ZzKrzXO6svzlQ' alt='Rodrigo Paz watching the election results in La Paz on Sunday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Governing math: Paz’s Christian Democratic Party does not hold a congressional majority, meaning he will need alliances to pass reforms [reuters.com#1].</li><li>Policy toolkit: He plans to invite more private investment and close loss-making state firms while keeping cash transfers for vulnerable groups [reuters.com#1].</li><li>End of MAS era: This runoff marked the first presidential race since 2005 without a candidate from Evo Morales’ MAS party, underscoring a political shift [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Family and origins: Paz is the son of former president Jaime Paz Zamora and was born in exile in Spain during Bolivia’s past military rule [reuters.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>This is a new stage for Bolivian democracy in the 21st century - Rodrigo Paz</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Rodrigo Paz: He frames the result as a democratic renewal and promises to seek consensus while pursuing market-friendly reforms. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/who-is-bolivias-new-president-rodrigo-paz-2025-10-20/'>Reuters</a>)</li><li>Paz supporters in La Paz: Supporters celebrated the outcome with joy, music, and fireworks in the streets, reflecting hopes for economic improvement. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329597/bolivia-holds-tight-run-voters-seek-president-lift-them-crisis'>SCMP</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251020-bolivia-turns-page-on-socialist-era-elects-great-nephew-of-1952-revolution-leader'>Bolivia turns page on Socialist era, elects great-nephew of 1952 revolution leader</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2025/10/20/paz-wins-bolivia-s-presidental-runoff'>Paz wins Bolivia&#x27;s presidental runoff</a> - mercopress.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/bolivia-centrist-paz-wins-presidency/a-74416997'>Bolivia: Centrist Paz wins presidency</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/20/bolivia-elects-centre-right-rodrigo-paz-as-president'>Bolivia elects centre-right Rodrigo Paz as president</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch'>Bolivia turns page on Socialist era, elects great-nephew of 1952 revolution leader • FRANCE 24</a> - youtube.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/centrist-rodrigo-paz-wins-bolivian-presidency-ending-nearly-20-years-of-leftist-rule'>Centrist Rodrigo Paz wins Bolivian presidency, ending nearly 20 years of leftist rule</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/20/bolivia-ends-two-decades-of-socialist-rule-as-center-right-rodrigo-paz-wins-presidency_6746588_4.html'>Bolivia ends two decades of socialist rule as center-right Rodrigo Paz wins presidency</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a hre